        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         If you look at a wizard by themselves, with no help from any other class to recover their mana, the gap closes a lot. Problem is, no matter how much mana a necro has, they are limited by buff slots and agro issues. So here are some solutions I came up with:</P><P>Solution 1. Give necros a DoT that closes the gap between them and wizards on raids, and they'll go and solo with it, making the solo necro comparable to a whole group.</P><P>Solution 2. Make a set of DoTs that ONLY work on mobs of specific types who summon. Main problem I see with this, is whole teams of necros dotting and maintaining their high DPS rather easily compared to wizards, making them at least as desirable on raids.</P><P>Solution 3. Reduce the agro on out DoTs. I mean LOW. Low enough that I can cast enough DoTs to do meaningful damage without getting agro before the wizard. Main problem I see with this, is necros stacking every dot they have outside of a raid environment.</P><P>Solution 4. Do nothing. This is the most cost effective solution for VI. Main problem I see with this, is people not buying PooP and VI gets slightly less money. Probably offset by whatever they'd have to pay someone to fix this stuff.</P><P><img src="http://chartermi.net/~gwealin/nennsig4.gif" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
